ked him, even though he had signed a three-year deal just a year earlier. T=
hey also jettisoned Andrew Cripps, their head of international distribution=
, who was quickly snapped up by Disney. Warners had recently disappointed i=
n its overseas releases of Twisters and Beetlejuice Beetlejuice, but the Go=
ldstine move mystified many people, who credit him with getting Dune: Part
One to a $411 million gross while the pandemic weighed on audiences, and th=
