as their first green light. That hardly felt like much of a statement: Who =
wouldn=E2=80=99t make a sequel to <em>Joker</em>, which had grossed $1 bill=
ion? De Luca and Abdy wouldn=E2=80=99t have received much credit if the mov=
ie was a hit.<br/><br/>But the gods were cruel, and when <em>Joker: Folie =
=C3=A0 Deux</em> went down in flames, they took some of the blame. Filmmake=
r <strong>Todd Phillips</strong> had not test-screened the movie, fearing l=
eaks. He did the same with the first movie, but that was a $55 million
proposition. The sequel was just a <em>bit</em> more expensive. =E2=80=9CYo=
u don=E2=80=99t allow the refusal to test-screen!=E2=80=9D a top executive =
at another studio almost shouted at me at the time. =E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99=
s no $200 million movie in the business that you don=E2=80=99t test-screen!=
 It=E2=80=99s utter malpractice!=E2=80=9D</p></div>
